n'''John D. Viener''' (born July 10, 1972) is an American actor, voice actor, writer, and comedian.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.latimes.com/business/realestate/hot-property/la-fi-hotprop-john-viener-windsor-square-home-20170711-story.html |title=\u2018Family Guy\u2019 writer-producer John Viener lists his 1920s home in Windsor Square |last=Leitereg |first=Neal J. |website=latimes.com |publisher=[[Los Angeles Times]] |location=Los Angeles, U.S. |access-date=2019-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005175346/http://www.latimes.com/business/realestate/hot-property/la-fi-hotprop-john-viener-windsor-square-home-20170711-story.html |archive-date=2018-10-05 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/john-viener-mather-zickel_b_3289307 |title=John Viener & Mather Zickel Lighten Up |last=Arabia |first=C. J. |last2=Editor |first2=ContributorSenior |date=2013-05-17 |website=HuffPost |publisher=[[HuffPost]] |location=New York, United States |access-date=2019-06-04}}</ref> Viener was born in [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]]. He is a writer and producer on the television series ''[[Family Guy]]'', where he also voices many miscellaneous characters.\n\nHe is also known as the voice of Norm the Robot on ''[[Phineas and Ferb]]''.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Actor/voice actor===\n*2002: ''[[Gilda Radner: It's Always Something]]'' - [[Chevy Chase]]\n*2002: ''[[The Late Late Show (CBS TV series)|The Late Late Show with Craig Kilborn]]'' - Himself\n*2003: ''[[The Support Group]]'' - John\n*2004: ''[[The Man in the Black Suit]]'' - The Man in the Black Suit\n*2004: ''[[The Act (short film)|The Act]]'' - Comedian\n*2005\u2013present: ''[[Family Guy]]'' - Miscellaneous characters\n*2005\u20132019: ''[[American Dad!]]'' - Miscellaneous characters\n*2005: ''[[The Late Late Show with Craig Ferguson]]'' - Weatherman Bob Fogg / Bob the Groom\n*2005: ''[[Arrested Development (TV series)|Arrested Development]]'' - Frank\n*2006: ''