159/https://www.myanmarevisa.gov.mm/ |archive-date=2013-10-19 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| 28 days\n| \n*eVisa holders must arrive via [[Yangon International Airport|Yangon]], [[Naypyidaw Airport|Nay Pyi Taw]] or [[Mandalay International Airport|Mandalay]] airports or via land border crossings with [[Thailand]] \u2014 [[Tachileik]], [[Myawaddy]] and [[Kawthaung]] or [[India]] \u2014 [[Rih Khaw Dar]] and [[Tamu, Myanmar|Tamu]].\n*eVisa available for both tourism (allowed stay is 28 days) or business purposes (allowed stay is 70 days).\n|-\n| {{flag|Namibia}}\n| {{yes-no|Visa on arrival}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=BG|destination=NA}}</ref>\n| 3 months\n|\n*Available at [[Hosea Kutako International Airport]].\n|-\n| {{flag|Nauru}}\n| {{no|Visa required}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=BG|destination=NR}}</ref>\n|\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Nepal}}\n| {{yes-no|Visa on arrival}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=BG|destination=NP}}</ref>\n| 90 days\n|\n|- \n| {{flag|Netherlands}} \n| {{free|{{sort|EU|Visa not required}}}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=BG|destination=NL}}</ref>\n| colspan=2| \n*[[Directive 2004/38/EC on the right to move and reside freely|Freedom of movement]] ([[European Netherlands]])\n*[[Bulgarian identity card|ID card]] valid \n|-\n| {{flag|New Zealand}}\n| {{yes2|[[Visa policy of New Zealand#Visa waiver countries|Electronic Travel Authority]]}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=BG|destination=NZ}}</ref>\n| 3 months\n|\n*International Visitor Conservation and Tourism Levy must be obtained alongside Electronic Travel Authority.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.immigration.govt.nz/new-zealand-visas/apply-for-a-visa/about-visa/nzeta|title=Information about NZeTA|website=Immigration New Zealand}}</ref>\n|- \n| {{flag|Nicaragua}}\n| {{yes|Visa not required}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=BG|destination=NI}}</ref>\n| 90 days\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Niger}}\n| {{no|Visa required}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=BG|destination=NE}}</ref>\n|\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Nigeria}}\n| {{no|Visa required}}<ref>{{Timatic|nation